 Hermès Logo
Hermès International S.A., or simply Hermès is a French high fashion luxury goods manufacturer established in 1837. It specializes in leather, lifestyle accessories, home furnishings, perfumery, jewellery, watches and ready-to-wear. Its logo, since the 1950s, is of a Duc carriage with horse. Nadège Vanhee-Cybulski is the current creative director. Source Meaning and history Hermes has progressed significantly from a pony saddlery maker to a notable brand selling calfskin, prepared-to-wear, embellishments, aromas, and gems.
